8.  Other duties of the municipal engineering/urban infrastructure specialist will be, but not 
limited to, the following: 

(i)  prepare a detailed work plan; 
(ii)  review published strategies and plans for the economic and structural development 
of Tacheng Baktu Liaota New Area, Yumin, E’min, and Tuoli municipal areas; 
(iii)  review and assess the proposed project component FSR from engineering and 
planning  perspectives  and  ensure  that  it  is  consistent  with  and  incorporates 
international good practice; 
(iv)  ensure project components are consistent with municipal and regional development 
programs, environmental protection programs, and social enhancement programs 
and coordinates with other infrastructure development projects (particularly those for 
associated utility services, including wastewater collection and treatment, and road 
development  program);  the  urban  development  reviewed  shall  including  short-, 
medium-, and long-term master plans and their phased implementation; 
(v)  critically review the proposed river training and flood control works through Tacheng 
City; recommend any changes to benefit strategic goals, and finalize feasibility-level 
designs for the flood protection and river training works; 
(vi)  finalize  feasibility-level  designs  for  the  windbreak  plantations  and  for  the 
construction/reconstruction of roads and associated services and facilities; 
(vii)  guide the water and sewerage engineer to assess and comment on the adequacy of 
water resources and present and future demands ensuring that a full water balance 
assessment is undertaken for Tacheng Baktu Liaota New Area and for E’min City; 
comment and advise on any anomalies or deficiencies;   
(viii)  finalize feasibility-level designs for water supply networks, wastewater collection 
sewers and wastewater treatment plant, and district heating distribution networks; 
and develop a water demand management plan to include the nonrevenue water 
management following guidelines from the ADB water operational plan; 
(ix)  undertake together with wastewater engineers an assessment of Tacheng City’s 
needs in terms of solid waste management and future plans of the municipality; 
(x)  check and validate urban population growth figures for Tacheng City and Yumin, 
E’min, and Tuoli county cities; 
(xi)  Identify investments opportunities in public transport facilities and non-motorized 
transport  facilities  along  the  transport  corridors,  entailing  the  development  of 
weather-protected public transport stations and the provision of priority treatments 
for public transport at key junctions;   
(xii)  ensure road safety during design and implementation process of the project roads, 
including identification of required project investments in road safety audits and 
consideration of key road safety interventions such as appropriate street lighting, 
safe  roadway  alignments,  adequate  shoulders,  signage,  roadway  markings, 
protective barriers in vulnerable areas, and  mechanisms to limit speeds along the 
corridor, especially in regard to crossings; 
(xiii)  coordinate with national consultants on industrial relocation/parks on incorporating 
their work inputs into PPTA reports; 
