15.  Wastewater and sewerage engineers (1.0 person-month, international; and 3.0 person-
months, national). The experts should be suitably qualified at professional level and have at least 
15  years  (international)  and  8  years  (national)  work  experience  in  wastewater treatment  and 
effluent disposal. They will be responsible for reviewing and commenting, the construction and 
operation of the new wastewater treatment plant, including the processing and disposal of sludge 
and the recycling of treated effluents and of the sewerage network. In particular the expert will: 

(i)  review and comment upon the existing status of the wastewater and sewerage 
sectors strategies and proposals for improving and strengthening the services of 
Tacheng City, and recommend changes and improvements to the approach and 
engineering process and detail; 
(ii)  assist the team leader to conduct sector and subsector assessment for the project; 
(iii)  review and assess the draft FSR and ensure that the wastewater and sewerage 
components  are  consistent  with  international  best  practices  and  Tacheng’s 
development policy and programs; 
(iv)  assist the team leader to conduct stakeholder workshops including a problem tree 
and objectives analysis and further refine the DMF; 
(v)  assist the team leader to develop comprehensive project rationale and the most 
relevant project impact and outcome statements, based on thorough analysis on the 
current conditions of water supply and wastewater collection and treatment system, 
catchments and the characteristics of wastewater in the catchments actual water 
use patterns, operating records of the existing facilities both on quantity and quality, 
clear calculation method for wastewater generation and collection, and verification 
of current and future demand projections; 
(vi)  review of parameters to be used in the design of the proposed sewerage systems 
and recommend any changes deemed appropriate; 
(vii)  lead technical review analysis of wastewater collection and treatment, effluent reuse, 
and sludge treatment and disposal by conducting a critical review on the FSR; 
(viii)  verify the wastewater treatment process based on a sound and detailed alternative 
analysis,  characterized  influent  quantity  and  quality,  required  effluent  quality 
standards, and operational aspects; 
(ix)  promote  beneficial  reuse  of  treated  effluent  and  sewage  sludge  and  provide 
necessary technical inputs to strengthen the project design to incorporate such 
beneficial reuse scheme;  
(x)  assist the team leader to prepare recommendations for strengthening, extending, 
and improving the government’s existing water management and water resources 
conservation,  including  the  balance  to  be  struck  between  structural  and 
nonstructural management measures; 
(xi)  develop policy and technical design options for treated wastewater to be used for 
irrigation; 
(xii)  recommend innovative features to enhance environmental sustainability, climate 
change resilience, and cost effectiveness; 
(xiii)  examine  possible  involvement  of  private  sector  in  investing  or  outsourcing  
Tacheng’s wastewater services, wherever possible; 
(xiv)  taking into account external factors such as population growth, review scale and 
capacity aspects of the wastewater plant component; 
